The paper presents an approach to model-based hierarchical clustering, which involves using a Bayesian analysis to organize data into a cluster hierarchy. This approach is applied specifically to the problem of document clustering, which suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or social and information networks (cs.SI).
